WEBVTT

00:46.505 --> 00:47.961
What's happening, Jonathan?

00:48.132 --> 00:49.542
[JONATHAN GRUNTING]

00:50.926 --> 00:51.961
[TRUCK CRASHES]

00:52.553 --> 00:53.884
Lex?

00:54.054 --> 00:56.136
Where are you?

01:18.454 --> 01:21.662
[YOUNG LEX WHIMPERING]

01:33.927 --> 01:35.542
[JONATHAN GRUNTS]

01:37.222 --> 01:39.338
[G ROANING]

02:45.707 --> 02:48.414
[PANTING]

03:02.933 --> 03:06.096
Lionel was too blind to see the truth.

03:09.481 --> 03:11.437
There was another.

04:05.454 --> 04:06.489
You did a very thorough job.

04:06.663 --> 04:07.652
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

04:09.291 --> 04:11.156
| just think that I'll take it from here.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.753
Goodbye.

04:14.922 --> 04:17.629
I think I'm ﬁnally ready
for the front page.

04:19.301 --> 04:21.917
-An article.
-I found a stack of missing-persons cases...

04:22.095 --> 04:24.006
...that no one is talking about.

04:24.181 --> 04:26.012
There's similarities between them all.

04:26.183 --> 04:28.799
This city is being attacked
and no one seems to care.

04:28.977 --> 04:33.596
Kind of makes you wish the red-blue blur
wasn't sitting down on the job.

04:34.691 --> 04:38.104
I think that these people were attacked
by the same criminal.

04:40.197 --> 04:42.859
Now, we can be the ﬁrst
to break this story.

04:43.116 --> 04:45.778
We can warn the people of Metropolis.

04:46.370 --> 04:47.826
I can't print this.

04:47.996 --> 04:49.372
You need to print it.

04:50.624 --> 04:52.956
No, they're called facts, Clark,
and you don't have any.

04:53.126 --> 04:55.378
You don't care about these victims?

04:58.715 --> 05:00.876
You're sweeping this under the rug.

05:01.385 --> 05:02.465
Great.

05:02.636 --> 05:05.002
Another conspiracy theory,
because I love those.

05:06.723 --> 05:08.224
Look closely.

05:08.392 --> 05:11.680
You will not ﬁnd a web of lies
behind this facade.

05:12.562 --> 05:14.553
That would be your department.

05:19.069 --> 05:21.731
[SOBS]

05:22.489 --> 05:24.571
A man who's not afraid to cry.

05:25.283 --> 05:27.695
-A man who's not afraid to cut onions.
-Ha, ha.

05:28.662 --> 05:30.368
You didn't have to cook me dinner...

05:30.539 --> 05:32.825
...though I did override your settings...

05:33.000 --> 05:35.582
...retrieve your addresses,
changed your applications...

05:35.752 --> 05:40.337
...so the next time you go ﬁshing for your
phone, you won't erase your whole world.

05:40.507 --> 05:41.622
Well, well, well.

05:41.800 --> 05:45.258
Ain't you the most over-achieving,
teacher's pet, know-it-all in the room.

05:45.429 --> 05:47.420
He's got a sense of humor
and he can cook.

05:47.597 --> 05:51.715
Well, the one thing that was on the menu
at the foster homes I grew up in:

05:51.935 --> 05:53.926
Mac and cheese.

05:57.983 --> 05:59.894
So have you heard from Jimmy lately?

06:03.697 --> 06:08.862
His last tirade of e-mails included every
single unﬂattering word in the dictionary...

06:09.036 --> 06:12.244
...including some that,
uh, didn't get past the censors.

06:13.582 --> 06:16.073
I thought he'd be dying
to get back together with you.

06:16.793 --> 06:18.294
No. Ha, ha.

06:18.962 --> 06:22.375
I believe that,
um, the last phrase he used was:

06:22.549 --> 06:26.883
"Don't call me, don't come by,
and if you e-mail me, I won't open it."

06:28.305 --> 06:29.385
Ouch.

06:29.556 --> 06:31.467
I thought we were best friends.

06:31.641 --> 06:33.802
But obviously there was some...

06:33.977 --> 06:36.969
...stuff brewing beneath the surface
for a while.

06:40.650 --> 06:45.986
How can you be so close to someone
and not really know who they are?

06:49.659 --> 06:50.694
[DAVIS GRUNTS]

06:50.869 --> 06:52.279
Davis.

06:53.497 --> 06:55.328
No, it's ﬁne. Chloe, it's ﬁne.

06:55.499 --> 06:56.830
Really. Um....

07:05.926 --> 07:07.166
Quick reﬂexes, huh?

07:10.764 --> 07:12.345
CLARK:
Chloe.

07:13.975 --> 07:15.761
Call much?

07:18.939 --> 07:20.145
Davis.

07:20.774 --> 07:22.230
Clark.

07:23.318 --> 07:26.025
Well, now that we have that
all worked out...

07:26.613 --> 07:28.524
...what's happening?

07:30.534 --> 07:34.026
l was working on a story I thought
you might have some information on.

07:35.497 --> 07:38.580
You know, I forgot something
I was supposed to do. I should go.

07:41.044 --> 07:42.204
What about dinner?

07:43.505 --> 07:46.087
Oh, you know, we'll do it tomorrow,
call it leftovers.

07:46.258 --> 07:47.668
-Okay.
-Thank you.

07:47.843 --> 07:49.003
[CHUCKLES]

07:57.394 --> 07:58.930
[G ROANS]

08:40.020 --> 08:41.726
Forgive me.

08:48.987 --> 08:51.103
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

08:55.869 --> 08:57.450
DAVIS:
Hello?

08:58.079 --> 08:59.285
TESS [OVER PHONE]:
I forget.

08:59.456 --> 09:02.448
What's the prayer
for dismembering a body?

09:31.863 --> 09:33.148
I can't believe this.

09:33.323 --> 09:36.656
There were over a dozen missing persons
last month alone.

09:36.826 --> 09:38.737
-You'd think it'd be newsworthy.
-Ha.

09:38.912 --> 09:42.700
Since when did newsworthy have anything
to do with what was on the front page?

09:48.838 --> 09:52.672
You know, Clark, I really hope you
have the safety cocked on your heat vision.

09:53.009 --> 09:54.419
What?

09:55.512 --> 09:59.630
You've been staring at the back of my head
so hard, my hair's gonna go up in ﬂames.

10:00.767 --> 10:04.180
| just didn't know you and Davis
were spending so much time together.

10:05.272 --> 10:07.479
-If you don't wanna talk about it--
-No, please.

10:07.649 --> 10:10.015
I love trudging through stagnant water.

10:11.194 --> 10:14.186
You're moving on fast
and I don't get what you see in the guy.

10:14.364 --> 10:15.900
First of all, it was dinner...

10:16.074 --> 10:19.817
...and secondly, he's kind, supportive
and a strong shoulder for me to lean on...

10:19.995 --> 10:23.658
...which, I don't know if you've realized,
but I could really use right now.

10:23.832 --> 10:27.541
Look, it's just I have a bad feeling
about the guy. I mean, come on, Chloe.

10:27.711 --> 10:29.542
Don't "Chloe" me, Clark.

10:29.713 --> 10:32.876
What is it with this meet-me-out-in-the-back
-for-a-duel mentality?

10:33.049 --> 10:36.917
Something to do with the fact that this guy
disappears, can't explain where he went.

10:37.095 --> 10:39.882
He's full of secrets.
There's not a record of his childhood.

10:40.348 --> 10:41.383
Sounds familiar.

10:42.600 --> 10:44.807
I don't collect crime-scene photos
in my locker.

10:44.978 --> 10:47.720
I'm not the ﬁrst EMT to show up
at every gruesome murder.

10:50.942 --> 10:52.227
What is it?

10:52.402 --> 10:55.769
A vehicle was found on ﬁre
just outside of Smallville.

10:56.489 --> 10:58.650
It has Davis' license plates.

11:11.755 --> 11:13.746
Were you expecting a chorus of angels?

11:13.923 --> 11:16.414
I'm sorry to disappoint you.

11:16.593 --> 11:19.175
I wanted to be here when you woke up.

11:20.889 --> 11:23.096
I apologize...

11:23.516 --> 11:25.723
...for the state that you're in.

11:26.895 --> 11:29.682
I didn't expect you to end up like this.

11:31.274 --> 11:33.435
l was trying to kill you.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.359
But...

11:37.781 --> 11:40.238
...that seems to be harder than I thought.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.785
[WHIMPERS]

11:44.704 --> 11:47.366
-Why am I here? Who are you?
-Shh.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.952
You're safe with me.

11:50.835 --> 11:52.450
Safer than out there.

11:53.171 --> 11:55.082
If the world knew you were a serial killer...

11:55.256 --> 11:58.293
...you'd be running from torches
for the rest of your life.

11:59.386 --> 12:02.423
You got the wrong idea about me, lady.

12:03.014 --> 12:07.348
It's not your fault
that you were born with a killer instinct.

12:08.770 --> 12:12.809
I even admire your altruistic selection
of victims.

12:13.483 --> 12:18.819
It's like keeping bats around to wipe out
the parasites that prey on the city.

12:22.492 --> 12:25.700
I can't control myself.

12:25.870 --> 12:28.156
I know you've tried to absolve yourself...

12:28.331 --> 12:29.662
...but...

12:30.667 --> 12:35.161
...even suicide wouldn't really work
for a guy who can't die, would it?

12:35.338 --> 12:39.672
I am not who you think I am.

12:41.177 --> 12:42.633
No.

12:44.639 --> 12:47.301
You're not who you think you are.

12:49.978 --> 12:51.343
[SCOFFS]

12:52.856 --> 12:54.642
And today...

12:54.816 --> 12:56.898
...you proved my theory.

12:57.152 --> 13:00.861
After I discovered
that you'd been a little unfriendly...

13:01.030 --> 13:03.362
...to a few Metropolis citizens...

13:03.533 --> 13:06.024
...I started looking into your background.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.367
The only problem is...

13:08.538 --> 13:10.529
...you don't have one.

13:10.874 --> 13:14.617
I thought I hit a dead end
until I inherited this.

13:16.588 --> 13:20.046
Stole it, if I'm being honest.

13:21.509 --> 13:24.672
I thought this might jog
your rusty memory.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.887
It was Lionel Luthor's.

13:28.933 --> 13:31.015
It tells a fascinating story...

13:31.186 --> 13:32.972
...about a boy who fell to Earth...

13:33.146 --> 13:36.855
...the day a meteor shower
destroyed a small Kansas town.

13:39.152 --> 13:42.736
I'm beginning to believe
the boy did not come here alone.

14:04.469 --> 14:05.675
[FOOTSTEPS NEARBY]

14:05.845 --> 14:09.303
JONATHAN: Kids just don't fall
out of the sky, Martha.

14:10.058 --> 14:12.140
MARTHA:
Then where did he come—?

14:12.936 --> 14:14.642
JONATHAN:
I don't know...

14:14.938 --> 14:17.304
...but he must have parents.

14:18.608 --> 14:21.771
Well, if he does,
they're deﬁnitely not from Kansas.

14:24.113 --> 14:26.650
Sweetheart, we can't keep him.

14:26.950 --> 14:29.942
What are we gonna tell people,
we found him out in a ﬁeld?

14:30.119 --> 14:32.280
We didn't ﬁnd him...

14:33.248 --> 14:35.204
...he found us.

14:53.935 --> 14:55.095
MAN:
Over here!

14:55.270 --> 14:56.476
I found him!

14:56.646 --> 14:59.558
[PANTING]

15:03.278 --> 15:04.984
[GRUNTING]

15:16.791 --> 15:18.497
[PANTING]

15:20.253 --> 15:21.993
YOUNG DAVIS:
No!

15:23.172 --> 15:25.754
[PANTING]

15:33.099 --> 15:34.930
YOUNG LEX:
Feathers.

15:36.352 --> 15:37.512
[WINGS FLAPPING]

15:38.813 --> 15:40.724
Feathers.

15:46.529 --> 15:48.861
[YOUNG DAVIS HUMMING]

16:14.057 --> 16:15.888
YOUNG DAVIS:
Who are you?

16:41.042 --> 16:42.327
Are you cold?

16:56.808 --> 16:58.469
Are you him?

16:58.768 --> 17:00.554
Are you Warrior Angel?

17:01.396 --> 17:02.886
No...

17:03.189 --> 17:05.054
...but I want to be.

17:19.288 --> 17:20.744
I'm Alexander.

17:20.915 --> 17:22.416
What's your name?

17:23.376 --> 17:24.616
I don't know.

17:25.545 --> 17:27.126
What are you doing in here?

17:27.296 --> 17:30.538
A man brought me here a few days ago.

17:31.467 --> 17:34.379
He made them put needles in me.

17:36.472 --> 17:39.134
But you don't look sick.

17:42.145 --> 17:43.635
Do you wanna play?

17:46.399 --> 17:48.014
Nobody will know.

17:48.192 --> 17:49.898
My dad went to some farm.

17:51.612 --> 17:53.022
Come on.

18:03.958 --> 18:06.040
TESS: The day the meteor shower
struck Smallville...

18:06.210 --> 18:08.872
...Lionel sent out a search party for you.

18:11.340 --> 18:13.672
Lionel had you taken from that ﬁeld...

18:13.843 --> 18:16.334
...because he thought
you were a prophesied messiah...

18:16.512 --> 18:18.548
...called the Traveler.

18:19.182 --> 18:22.766
A visitor from another planet
sent to save humankind.

18:22.935 --> 18:25.096
But what Lionel didn't realize...

18:25.271 --> 18:28.684
...is that there were two boys
that fell to Earth that day.

18:31.194 --> 18:33.230
The Traveler...

18:34.489 --> 18:35.854
...and you.

18:40.286 --> 18:42.652
[TOW TRUCK BEEPING]

18:55.218 --> 18:56.628
Excuse me.

18:58.346 --> 18:59.711
Have the police been here yet?

18:59.889 --> 19:01.720
Come and gone.

19:02.934 --> 19:04.014
Did they ﬁnd a victim?

19:04.185 --> 19:06.346
The thing was abandoned.

19:06.562 --> 19:08.393
No sign of a driver.

19:10.483 --> 19:12.019
Thank you.

19:20.076 --> 19:21.065
Clark?

19:21.244 --> 19:23.075
What's going on?

19:23.287 --> 19:25.278
It's weird
that Davis would've stopped here.

19:25.456 --> 19:26.491
Why?

19:26.666 --> 19:28.497
What's here?

19:28.793 --> 19:31.205
This is the ﬁeld where my ship landed.

19:34.006 --> 19:37.624
That's a pretty big coincidence pill
to swallow.

19:41.430 --> 19:44.342
This place must hold a lot of memories
for you, huh?

19:52.525 --> 19:55.858
Chloe, memories aren't the only thing buried
in that ﬁeld.

20:06.747 --> 20:08.578
[GASPS]

20:09.667 --> 20:11.453
[GRUNTS]

20:38.154 --> 20:40.145
[BOYS GRUNTING]

20:49.665 --> 20:50.950
[BOTH GRUNTING]

21:05.431 --> 21:06.466
What is that?

21:07.016 --> 21:09.177
YOUNG LEX:
It's made from the armor of St. George.

21:09.352 --> 21:13.846
He slayed dragons
with his sword called Ascalon.

21:16.108 --> 21:19.521
I am St. George and you are the dragon.

21:19.695 --> 21:23.688
You have been sent to destroy the world
but only I can protect it...

21:23.866 --> 21:26.357
...from a beast like you.

21:26.535 --> 21:29.698
Fight or die.

21:32.875 --> 21:35.332
[GASPING]

21:37.880 --> 21:39.381
[YOUNG DAVIS GASPS]

21:41.384 --> 21:44.842
l have slayed the beast.

21:45.012 --> 21:49.005
I am the victor,
and I shall claim my treasure.

21:55.064 --> 21:56.395
[SCREAMS]

21:56.899 --> 21:58.514
-What's wrong?
-It hurt!

21:58.693 --> 21:59.978
-Are you okay?
-It hurt!

22:00.152 --> 22:02.359
[YELLS]

22:02.530 --> 22:04.020
[PANTING]

22:06.659 --> 22:08.320
[YOUNG DAVIS COUGHS]

22:15.209 --> 22:16.915
There's a way.

22:23.426 --> 22:25.132
You think you can keep me here?

22:25.302 --> 22:28.715
I know.
There's nothing that can restrain you.

22:31.600 --> 22:33.511
Then what are you gonna do?

22:34.520 --> 22:38.513
I've been asking myself that question
for the last few hours.

22:40.109 --> 22:43.442
What do you do
when you ﬁnd Judas in your midst?

22:44.655 --> 22:48.113
Who would Christ have been
if Judas had not betrayed him?

22:48.284 --> 22:52.197
Maybe we would remember Jesus
as only a teacher roaming the desert.

22:53.622 --> 22:55.829
I don't quite understand
what you're getting at.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.412
Without Judas,
Jesus would've never risen from the dead...

22:58.586 --> 23:01.828
...to come back
and face his greatest challenge...

23:04.633 --> 23:06.544
...saving humankind.

23:08.387 --> 23:10.969
There is a savior among us.

23:11.807 --> 23:13.763
You are here to betray him.

23:17.188 --> 23:18.724
I haven't betrayed anyone.

23:20.816 --> 23:24.149
I ﬁnally realized
that until you fulﬁll your destiny...

23:24.320 --> 23:27.312
...he won't have his great challenge
to overcome.

23:27.490 --> 23:29.651
He cannot become the world's savior...

23:29.825 --> 23:32.817
...without triumphing
over the world's destroyer.

23:35.998 --> 23:37.659
-What savior?
-Unh!

23:37.833 --> 23:39.994
What are you talking about?

23:41.003 --> 23:41.992
Clark.

23:43.130 --> 23:45.837
There's a reason
that you two don't get along.

23:46.926 --> 23:48.917
You were destined to kill each other.

23:53.557 --> 23:55.468
[DAVIS GRUNTING]

24:02.358 --> 24:05.600
The guy blacks out regularly
and you chose not to mention it?

24:05.778 --> 24:07.689
I ﬁgured he had low blood sugar
or something.

24:07.863 --> 24:10.115
He told you
he was hiding something dark inside.

24:10.282 --> 24:15.072
-That didn't set off any alarms for you?
-I ﬁgured "dark" meant moody or bipolar.

24:15.246 --> 24:17.407
I don't exactly jump right to serial killer.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.537
You were angry at me for doubting him.

24:19.708 --> 24:21.209
I know, okay?

24:21.377 --> 24:23.333
l was in denial. l--

24:23.504 --> 24:24.869
You know, |--

24:25.047 --> 24:27.129
I couldn't believe that it was this bad.

24:27.299 --> 24:28.960
It's not that bad, Chloe.

24:29.135 --> 24:30.966
It's worse.

24:32.972 --> 24:35.839
| just can't believe
he's the serial killer that--

24:36.600 --> 24:38.886
That Jimmy warned us about.

24:43.065 --> 24:45.181
I did some checking
into these missing persons.

24:45.359 --> 24:47.850
They're not exactly Metropolis' ﬁnest.

24:48.028 --> 24:50.565
Assault charges,
breaking and entering, abuse.

24:50.739 --> 24:53.025
You think Davis
is on some sort of vigilante mission?

24:53.200 --> 24:54.360
He was until last night.

24:54.535 --> 24:57.902
I mean, he's not stupid enough
to abandon his car next to a--

24:58.247 --> 25:00.704
A ﬁeld full of evidence.

25:00.916 --> 25:02.827
Chloe,
| get the feeling someone took him.

25:03.002 --> 25:05.414
When I was looking into Davis' past...

25:05.588 --> 25:08.421
...his county records
had already been checked out by someone.

25:10.217 --> 25:13.709
I think it's time to pay a visit
to the widow of LuthorCorp.

25:17.725 --> 25:19.807
We tried to stop him.
We opened ﬁre, but he--

25:19.977 --> 25:23.060
Find him or don't come back.

25:31.614 --> 25:35.607
Tess? Look, I know
you've been looking into Davis Bloome.

25:36.118 --> 25:37.528
He did this, didn't he?

25:37.703 --> 25:40.786
I'm afraid there's not a short version
of that story.

25:41.790 --> 25:43.075
I think I missed something.

25:43.250 --> 25:45.787
No, you've been at the center of it
the whole time.

25:46.962 --> 25:50.045
I came into possession of a journal
of Lionel Luthor's.

25:51.008 --> 25:55.251
The journal talks about a boy who fell from
the stars on the day of a meteor shower.

25:55.429 --> 26:00.719
Lionel's obsession with this Traveler was
the reason he was in Smallville that day.

26:00.893 --> 26:04.260
He wanted to possess the Traveler
for himself.

26:04.438 --> 26:05.769
Why are you telling me all this?

26:05.940 --> 26:10.684
Because Lionel, and then Lex,
got the moral of the story wrong.

26:12.238 --> 26:16.777
According to the Kawatche Indians,
this boy is part of a two-headed creature.

26:17.201 --> 26:19.988
Good and evil.

26:20.162 --> 26:24.155
The Luthors were too busy feuding over
which one of them was worthy enough...

26:24.333 --> 26:28.292
...to be your adversary
that they couldn't see the truth...

26:30.506 --> 26:34.294
...that there was another boy
who came to Earth with you.

26:36.345 --> 26:37.630
Davis Bloome.

26:38.222 --> 26:39.553
[CHUCKLES]

26:40.599 --> 26:44.091
So you think that Davis Bloome and I
are from another planet?

26:44.270 --> 26:46.977
Lionel found Davis
on the day of the meteor shower.

26:47.147 --> 26:50.856
He thought he was the Traveler,
but then the boy's tests seemed normal.

26:52.027 --> 26:53.437
Lionel was holding Davis?

26:53.612 --> 26:55.113
Only for ﬁve days.

26:55.281 --> 26:57.488
And then he threw the boy
out onto the street...

26:57.658 --> 27:00.115
...because he got a phone call
from Martha Kent.

27:00.661 --> 27:01.901
[CHUCKLES]

27:02.079 --> 27:04.536
-Tess, you're reaching.
-Am I?

27:04.707 --> 27:07.449
It's Lionel's own words, and | quote:

27:07.626 --> 27:10.208
"I have the wrong boy...

27:11.046 --> 27:13.537
...but I believe
that l have found the true Traveler."

27:14.383 --> 27:16.920
Why would Lionel Luthor
arrange an adoption for a boy...

27:17.094 --> 27:19.631
...who seemed to come
out of nowhere?

27:22.266 --> 27:25.474
Looks like you're the reason that
Davis was abandoned in the ﬁrst place.

27:34.695 --> 27:36.231
[DOOR CLOSES]

27:37.823 --> 27:40.690
What did the LuthorCorp diva
have to say?

27:44.038 --> 27:46.324
I know what you've done.
Jimmy was right.

27:46.498 --> 27:47.954
Uh....

27:48.417 --> 27:50.578
That guy that I killed...

27:50.753 --> 27:53.335
...he was a drunk driver.
He was a three-time offender.

27:53.505 --> 27:55.211
And what about all the others?

27:55.382 --> 27:57.998
Are you gonna try and justify
killing them too?

27:58.177 --> 28:01.340
No, I didn't know what else to do!
I'm sorry.

28:01.930 --> 28:04.057
-You lied to me!
-I had to.

28:04.224 --> 28:07.057
-I didn't wanna drag you into this.
-Then why are you here?

28:12.399 --> 28:13.559
I love you.

28:15.694 --> 28:18.276
And I need to know
if you care about me.

28:19.990 --> 28:22.527
How can you ask me that?

28:24.119 --> 28:25.700
I thought I did.

28:27.122 --> 28:28.987
[SIGHS]

28:30.459 --> 28:32.950
Then I need you to do something for me.

28:34.129 --> 28:37.462
I won't do anything for you.

28:40.094 --> 28:42.801
I need you to help me die.

28:57.945 --> 28:59.560
Chloe?

29:10.707 --> 29:12.413
Dr. Groll's lab.

29:12.876 --> 29:14.457
Chloe.

29:34.857 --> 29:36.518
It's time.

29:38.026 --> 29:39.812
I can't.

29:40.696 --> 29:42.186
I'm
sorry

29:42.364 --> 29:44.696
I ﬁnally found a way out of this.

29:44.867 --> 29:46.323
Don't take that away from me.

29:47.286 --> 29:48.901
Please.

29:50.038 --> 29:51.949
Pull the lever, Chloe.

30:01.175 --> 30:02.836
[SIGHS]

30:08.056 --> 30:10.388
[SOBBING]
I can't kill you, Davis.

30:14.980 --> 30:16.516
Chloe, what are you doing?

30:16.690 --> 30:18.191
DAVIS:
It's my life, Clark.

30:18.358 --> 30:20.144
I can take it if I choose.

30:20.319 --> 30:21.684
Davis, don't be a martyr.

30:21.862 --> 30:23.477
That's not what this is, Clark.

30:23.655 --> 30:25.737
DAVIS:
I'm not doing this for you.

30:25.908 --> 30:29.696
I want this to end.
I can't live with myself.

30:29.870 --> 30:31.576
But it's not your fault.

30:31.747 --> 30:34.955
Everything's that's happened to you
is because of me, all right?

30:35.125 --> 30:36.410
We should've been brothers.

30:38.086 --> 30:40.338
Davis, you didn't have a home.

30:40.881 --> 30:42.417
If that would've happened to me--

30:43.258 --> 30:47.627
I've wondered what it would have been like
if the Luthors had found me in that ﬁeld.

30:48.388 --> 30:50.174
I could've turned out differently.

30:50.349 --> 30:52.135
But you didn't.

30:52.309 --> 30:54.766
You were destined to have the better life.

30:55.437 --> 30:57.723
And no matter how hard we try
to ﬁght it...

30:57.898 --> 31:02.688
...we will always return
to our true nature.

31:06.281 --> 31:08.738
Chloe, pull the lever. Let me end this.

31:13.288 --> 31:15.404
DAVIS:
Enough, Clark.

31:15.958 --> 31:19.246
You know that you should let me die.

31:19.920 --> 31:22.286
Davis,
there has to be something in your life...

31:22.464 --> 31:25.126
...something that is worth giving it
one more try.

31:32.140 --> 31:37.726
It isn't always about where your heart is.

31:38.313 --> 31:41.100
It's about what you've done...

31:41.275 --> 31:43.641
...and what you're going to do.

31:46.238 --> 31:49.321
I was sent here to destroy you, Clark.

31:53.787 --> 31:55.027
[SIGHS]

31:55.205 --> 31:56.490
Clark.

31:56.665 --> 31:58.326
[GRUNTING]

31:58.500 --> 32:00.582
-Davis! Davis!
-Unh!

32:00.752 --> 32:07.464
There aren't enough prayers in this world
to give me redemption!

32:07.634 --> 32:09.010
-C|ark!
CLARK: No!

32:11.305 --> 32:13.045
[DAVIS GRUNTS]

32:22.357 --> 32:24.268
[GRUNTS]

32:47.382 --> 32:49.464
What are we doing here?

32:50.218 --> 32:53.210
I was told to drop you off here.

32:54.806 --> 32:57.013
But who's gonna meet me?

33:04.149 --> 33:05.514
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

33:57.369 --> 33:58.734
[SOBS SOFTLY]

34:13.051 --> 34:14.211
How you holding up?

34:15.262 --> 34:17.298
I've had better days.

34:23.270 --> 34:25.807
That's saying a lot in Smallville.

34:28.984 --> 34:30.599
And, uh, Davis'....

34:36.575 --> 34:39.567
I spoke to Oliver.
He's taking care of the details.

34:42.831 --> 34:44.787
We need to talk about what happened.

34:46.168 --> 34:48.159
I wouldn't change what I did.

34:48.920 --> 34:50.660
But there's always another way.

34:50.839 --> 34:53.330
He could have killed you, Clark.

34:54.676 --> 34:58.840
I won't risk the safety of the world
because of your code of ethics...

34:59.723 --> 35:02.681
...because you refuse to stop the things
that threaten you.

35:09.983 --> 35:13.020
Jor-El said he was the ultimate destroyer.

35:13.737 --> 35:16.069
Didn't turn out to be much of a ﬁght.

35:35.801 --> 35:38.713
When I was a kid,
I used to have this nightmare.

35:39.638 --> 35:42.380
My ship landed in a ﬁeld
and no one ever found me.

35:43.558 --> 35:46.800
That nightmare was Davis' life.

35:48.396 --> 35:52.480
I always felt like it was a burden
knowing that I was destined to save people.

35:54.277 --> 35:56.393
I can't imagine
what it must have felt like...

35:56.571 --> 35:59.904
...knowing that no matter
how you lived your life, you were doomed.

36:19.553 --> 36:22.420
The new, contemplative Clark Kent.

36:22.639 --> 36:24.254
I like it.

36:24.558 --> 36:25.764
I'm kind of busy.

36:25.934 --> 36:27.094
With what?

36:27.269 --> 36:29.134
Farm chores?

36:30.272 --> 36:34.106
I'd let you off
if you were saving a busload of children...

36:34.276 --> 36:36.267
...but cleaning the feeding bin?

36:36.444 --> 36:38.821
I'm really sorry that you bought
into this...

36:38.989 --> 36:41.526
...strange obsession
that the Luthors had for me, but—

36:41.700 --> 36:43.941
I don't think of it as buying in.

36:45.453 --> 36:46.863
I think of it as believing.

36:47.330 --> 36:50.618
If you spend your Saturday nights
reading the journal of a madman...

36:50.792 --> 36:54.125
...sounds to me like you have a few holes
in your personal life.

36:55.422 --> 36:57.287
We all look to idols...

36:57.465 --> 36:58.671
...religion...

36:58.842 --> 37:01.879
...the rich and the famous,
because we have holes in our lives.

37:02.929 --> 37:05.136
It doesn't mean
that these things aren't real.

37:06.808 --> 37:09.641
What you've made me out to be
is not real.

37:10.145 --> 37:11.635
I'll never be that man.

37:12.522 --> 37:15.184
Not until Judas is at your back.

37:17.527 --> 37:20.735
I have this feeling
that you'll never fulﬁll your great destiny...

37:20.906 --> 37:23.613
...until you meet your greatest challenge.

37:24.910 --> 37:26.992
You don't know anything about my life.

37:28.997 --> 37:33.582
If this is the way that you lied to Lex, then I
can see how it pushed him over the edge.

37:34.753 --> 37:37.665
Lex was racing toward that drop-off
way before he met me.

37:38.423 --> 37:40.505
Yeah, but betrayal....

37:42.260 --> 37:45.172
You know, the more you love someone,
the harder it is.

37:45.764 --> 37:47.004
Are you threatening me?

37:49.351 --> 37:51.012
I'm not that naive.

37:53.980 --> 37:56.357
I'm not some problem to be solved.

37:57.692 --> 37:59.273
I get it.

38:00.695 --> 38:02.686
It's too early.

38:04.324 --> 38:06.940
Just know that I'll wait for you, Clark.

38:08.161 --> 38:10.652
I'll wait for you to come to me.

38:12.791 --> 38:14.702
It's gonna be a long wait.

38:23.843 --> 38:27.051
It'll be shorter than you think, Kal-El.

39:20.150 --> 39:21.856
[CLATTERING NEARBY]

39:28.491 --> 39:30.072
[CLATTERING CONTINUES]

39:42.005 --> 39:43.245
[CLATTERING NEARBY]

40:05.820 --> 40:06.809
DAVIS:
Don't be afraid.

40:12.535 --> 40:14.321
You're alive.

40:14.913 --> 40:16.619
The meteor rocks didn't—

40:16.790 --> 40:18.621
They made me stronger.

40:20.919 --> 40:23.501
So are you now...

40:23.671 --> 40:24.831
...invulnerable?

40:29.344 --> 40:31.005
I'm immortal.

40:33.389 --> 40:35.846
Then that means Clark's in danger.

40:36.017 --> 40:39.384
No matter what you want,
the other side of you will try and kill him.

40:39.562 --> 40:42.053
I won't kill Clark if I'm with you.

40:43.650 --> 40:45.186
What?

40:46.861 --> 40:48.601
What do I have to do with any of this?

40:48.780 --> 40:54.366
There's something about being around you
that seems to calm the murderer inside me.

40:56.996 --> 40:59.533
But you said so yourself.
It's your true nature.

40:59.707 --> 41:01.322
[SIGHS]

41:02.127 --> 41:06.587
But maybe there's something
stronger out there than my need to kill.

41:12.011 --> 41:14.218
Will you stay with me?

42:34.510 --> 42:36.501
[ENGLISH SDH]
